 This collection of Abrams’s writings gathers speeches, articles, debates, briefs, oral arguments, and testimony from his entire career. The writings illuminate topics of ongoing import: WikiLeaks, the correctness of the Citizens United case, journalist shield laws, and, not least, the responsibilities of the press. An exceptional writer and a brilliant thinker, Abrams offers a unique perspective on the First Amendment and the unparalleled rights it confers.  afunded by Karen Gantz Zahler Literary Management  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFreedom of expressionzUnited States. 0aLawyerszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aLAW / Constitutional.2bisacsh2 aKaren Gantz Zahler Literary Managementefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030019087840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019503340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300195033423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300195033/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY